      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To ensure a 0% stockout rate, we need to calculate the order quantity for each item based on the lead time and standard deviation. \n\nFor Product A, with a lead time of 2 weeks and a standard deviation of 50, we can use the following formula:\n\nOrder Quantity = (Weekly Demand x Lead Time) / Standard Deviation\n= (500 x 2) / 50\n= 20 units\n\nFor Product B, with a lead time of 1 week and a standard deviation of 15, we can use the following formula:\n\nOrder Quantity = (Weekly Demand x Lead Time) / Standard Deviation\n= (50 x 1) / 15\n= 3.33 units\n\nFor Product C, with a lead time of 3 days and a standard deviation of 400, we can use the following formula:\n\nOrder Quantity = (Weekly Demand x Lead Time) / Standard Deviation\n= (2000 x 7) / 400\n= 35 units\n\nSo, the order quantities we need to set are 20 units for Product A, 3.33 units for Product B, and 35 units for Product C.",
